speech.p:
asked the Minister of Health (1) what steps he has taken to comply with the declaration made against him in the case of Barber versus Manchester Regional Hospital Board and the Minister of Health that, in failing to comply with Clause 16 of the Terms and Conditions of Service, he was in breach of statutory duty;

(2) whether he is aware that Mr. A. H. Barber who was awarded damages


against the Minister for wrongful dismissal has still not been offered any employment in the National Health Service; and what action he proposes to take in this matter.
